Daredevil suspected Fulani Herdsmen yesterday attacked the Afuze Divisional Police Headquarters killing its DPO, pregnant officer and four others.
The attackers who were said to have invaded the isolated police atation burning down the building and cars in the premises Freed six of its colleagues who were being detained at the Police Station.
Eyewitnesses disclosed that the reinforcements that was sent by the Edo Commissioner of Police rearrested three of the six detainees freed by the attackers.
Among those killed was the Divisional Police Chief, a pregnant woman police and three other officers.
